            "role": "assistant",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Aye, matey, ye’ve got yerself a fine day ahead, warm and sunny like the golden treasure o’ the seas! If ye be chartin’ a course ashore, light and breezy garb be the way to go. \n\nSlip on a trusty shirt, cotton or linen, to keep ye cool as a ship on calm waters. Pair it with some shorts, aye, but naught too tight—ye wouldn’t want to feel like yer walkin’ the plank, eh? Comfortable shoes or sandals will keep yer feet feelin’ grand, fit for a fine round o' adventurin'.\n\nAnd don’t forget yer hat, a wide-brimmed one to shield ye noggin from the sun’s rays, lest ye end up lookin' like a lobster who fell overboard! Sling on some sunscreen too, or ye’ll take home a mighty sunburn instead o’ gold. \n\nArrr, dress with the ease o’ the breeze, and ye’ll be set to conquer the day. What say ye, shipmate?",
